The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 13 October is 4,093 (473.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 09 October, there were 354 new confirmed cases (41.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 October, there were 239 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 48% ( 115 extra cases).
